-- Yankees-Tigers Game 4 of ALCS Is Postponed by Rain in Detroit
-- B y   E r i k   M a t u s z e w s k i
-- 2012-10-18T01:25:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-18/yankees-tigers-game-4-of-alcs-is-postponed-by-rain-in-detroit.html
Game 4 of the American League
Championship Series between the  New York Yankees  and Detroit
Tigers has been postponed until tomorrow because of rain.  The Tigers hold a three-games-to-none lead in the best-of-
seven Major League Baseball playoff series. They can advance to
the World Series with a win in Game 4, which has been
rescheduled for 4:07 p.m. Eastern time tomorrow in Detroit.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Erik Matuszewski at 
 matuszewski@bloomberg.net  